The first line of defense that can be used to reduce the risk of infection is to wear masks; the use of surgical masks and dustproof N95 masks (1860s series) can help control the spread of the virus.
Surgical masks prevent droplets from a potential infected person from spreading through the air or sticking to the surfaces of objects that may be passed on to others.
However, only N95 (Series 1860s) masks prevent the inhalation of viruses small to 10 to 80 nm, and only 5% of viruses can fully penetrate; SARS-CoV-2 is similar in size to SARS-CoV, all about 85 nm.
