In this review, we provide an overview of the origins, species-to-species transmission and mechanisms of HCoV in humans and animals.
In particular, we highlighted and explored a common theme that HCoV progeny viruses are usually not pathogenic in their natural storage hosts, but are pathogenic after spreading across species to new hosts.
In addition, we also reviewed the evolutionary trend of HCoV, in which the increase in transmissibility is often accompanied by a decrease in pathogenicity.
